  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a single axis tag and design-space value that together specify one dimension of a variable font's design position.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate` pairs a four-byte axis tag (such as `wght`
for weight) with a floating-point design-space value. An array of these
coordinates is used in <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments.VariationDesignPosition>
to define the full position within a variable font's design space when calling
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone*>.

This is a value type; no disposal is required.

## Examples

```csharp
var position = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
{
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700f },
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wdth"), Value = 75f },
};
var args = new SKFontArguments { VariationDesignPosition = position };
using var customTypeface = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
